!!!HAO:    For a long time the Pawnee have called the cedar
!!!HAO: tree "mother," a custom which had its origin in the
!!!HAO: dream of a man who saw a cedar tree and thought it
!!!HAO: was "like a woman."  He said, "This tree is made to
!!!HAO: look the same in winter and summer, and to stand up
!!!HAO: so nicely.  The leaves of other trees fall but this
!!!HAO: tree is always green."  This strange woman-tree made
!!!HAO: a noise like a bear and the song is used in the Bear
!!!HAO: dance.
!!!HTX:    He said, a woman is here standing among the trees,
!!!HTX: Now I am telling it,
!!!HTX: A woman is here standing among the trees,
!!!HTX: Loudly does she stand among the trees,
!!!HTX: From where her spirit dwells she grunts (like a bear).
